blog.name: homosociallyyours
blog.title: i am a homosocialsexual
blog.description:
megan/39/she&they pronouns. 
please be 18+ if you follow me.
queer, fat, genderqueer femme. geeky, nerdy, and really into cheese. seriously. 
i reblog a lot of queer and gay things; femmeslash of many varieties, sherlock (johnlock, johnlockstrade, not mad at mary morstan, not happy about s4 but not super salty either), 1D (ot5 &ot4, larrie/harrie/louie, don't come at me with negativity about any one of my darling boys), star wars (carrie fisher/space mom), and a multitude of other fandoms that are all over the place; and really anything else that strikes my fancy, including some things that may be nsfw. oh, and martin freeman. i love him. in a truly filthy way. 
i write, i draw, i squeal over things i love. i live for getting to know new people, so please don't hesitate to send me a message about all the things. always.

blog.name: latenightlarrythoughts
blog.title: Harry and Louis.
blog.description: Emily. 19. Music lover. Harry. Louis. Larry. Thoughts. LoveisLove. Mostly Larry stuff. Ask me things.

summary:
Lyric Analysis: Woman 
So I know that this song may sound like Harry is talking about a woman he likes but here’s my perceptive...
body:
Lyric Analysis: Woman

So I know that this song may sound like Harry is talking about a woman he likes but here’s my perceptive on it.

I’m selfish, I know, But I don’t ever want to see you with him, I’m selfish, I know, I told you, but I know you never listen.“

Harry is talking to Eleanor and telling her that he’s s selfish and doesn’t want to see her with Louis, he has told her this many times but she/management refuses to listen to him.

"I hope you can see the shape that I’m in, While he’s touching your skin, He’s right where I should, where I should be, But you’re making me bleed”

Harry hopes that Eleanor can see the pain she is causing him while he is forced to watch Louis pretend to be with her, and dreads on the fact that Louis is somewhere he should be with him but Eleanor keeps getting in the way.

“Woman, Woman (la la la la la) W-Woman”

Harry calls her woman by doing this he takes away the factor that he is talking about a love interest where as normally you’d call someone you know want or like a pet name.

“Tempted, you know, Apologies are never gonna fix this, i’m empty, I know, Promises are broken like a stich is.”

Harry is tempted to give up on pretending he’s s fine and just come out with Louis because Eleanors apologies arent fixing how he feels,he’s empty and the promises that are made continue to be broken,these promises could be things eleanor/ management may have promised to Harry like how long the her and Louis relationship would last or how far they would go to prove it.

So overall i don’t believe this song is about a woman Harry likes or wants but instead a woman he envy’s because she is with the guy he wants to be with.
